ilable in both English and Spanish.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/51VZgJ1jsTL.jpg?v=1758407351', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","clinical-veterinary-advisor","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10749090234671', 'Common Clinical Presentations in Dogs and Cats 1st Edition', 39, 'Your Quick Reference for Canine and Feline Clinical Presentations This book is a reliable resource and quick reference for diagnosing canine and feline patients , based on presenting complaints. The text takes a problem-oriented approach to recognizing common clinical conditions and introduces diagnostic and treatment plans for companion animal practice. Key Features Problem-Oriented Approach : The text takes a problem-oriented approach to recognizing common clinical conditions and introduces diagnostic and treatment plans for companion animal practice. Organized by Body System : The book presents 78 chapters grouped by body system for ease of access, with each chapter focusing on identifying the chief complaint, pinpointing possible diagnoses, and determining the clinical approach to patient care. Standardized Format : A standardized chapter format for ease of use. Visual Learning : The book is richly illustrated throughout with color photographs and line drawings that demonstrate the conditions discussed. Fast Access : It gives clinicians fast access to essential details for approaching common case presentations in dogs and cats and forming a correct diagnosis. Broad Audience : Written for small animal general practitioners and veterinary students , this book is a patient-side reference that can help practitioners gain the knowledge and confidence to correctly diagnose a wide range of clinical presentations.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/Screenshot2025-09-19at6.05.40PM.webp?v=1758323193', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10749106028847', 'Fundamentals of Canine Neuroanatomy and Neurophysiology 1st Edition', 35, 'Your Visual Guide to Canine Neuroanatomy and Neurophysiology This book is a comprehensive guide to the fundamentals of veterinary neuroanatomy and neurophysiology . It introduces the structure and function of the nervous system and demonstrates its relevance to clinical applications with a highly visual approach. Key Features Comprehensive Introduction : It offers a straightforward yet comprehensive introduction to the structure and function of the nervous system. Clinical Relevance : The book demonstrates the relevance of the basic principles of neuroanatomy and neurophysiology to the clinical setting. Extensive Visuals : It illustrates concepts using line drawings, photographs, micrographs, and MRIs . Companion Website : It includes access to a companion website with review questions and answers and the figures from the book. Broad Audience : It is a useful guide for veterinary students and practitioners who want to deepen their understanding of neuroanatomy and neurophysiology.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/61eGpBxRAaL._SL1294.jpg?v=1758327269', '', 'Cats', '["cat","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10744493637935', 'Zoo and Wild Animal Dentistry', 59, 'Your Comprehensive Guide to Zoo and Wild Animal Dentistry Zoo and Wild Animal Dentistry is the first book to offer a comprehensive reference to oral pathology and dental therapy in captive and wild exotic animals. This groundbreaking resource is filled with instructive photographs and illustrations that clearly depict pathologies and demonstrate techniques, making it an essential guide for the dental care of these often-neglected species. Key Features Comprehensive Coverage : This book is a comprehensive reference to oral pathology and dental therapy in a wide range of species, including cats, bears, primates, dogs, raccoons, weasels, hyenas, marsupials, herbivores, edentates, sea mammals, birds, and reptiles . It provides oral descriptions for each of the more than 300 species included in the book. Groundbreaking Resource : It is the first book to offer a comprehensive reference to oral pathology and dental therapy in captive and wild exotic animals. Practical Guidance : It offers a reliable resource to the history of veterinary dentistry, information on the evolution of teeth, practical dental therapeutics, and oral descriptions for each of the species. Latest Advances : The book includes information on the most recent advances in the field. Expert Authorship : It is authored by noted experts on the topic who draw on their years of experience with exotic animals. Target Audience : It is a must-have resource for zoo and wildlife caretakers and veterinarians, veterinary dentists, veterinary technicians , and veterinary students .', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/91a-wKvwKwL._SL1500.jpg?v=1757790100', '', 'Cats', '["cat","dentistry-1","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10744468275503', 'Veterinary Periodontology 1st Edition', 29, 'Your User-Friendly Guide to Veterinary Periodontology This book is a comprehensive yet user-friendly reference on periodontal disease in dogs and cats , encompassing etiology, pathogenesis, and clinical features. Emphasizing the clinical management of this common dental disease, this book covers both basic and advanced treatments, offering practical instruction on therapeutic procedures. Key Features Step-by-Step Procedures : The book presents detailed information in an accessible format, including numerous step-by-step procedures for use in the clinic. Veterinary-Specific Information : This book builds on existing human-based knowledge to provide veterinary-specific information on the periodontal disease process, therapies, patient management, and instrumentation. Clinical Management : It emphasizes the clinical management of this common dental disease, covering both basic and advanced treatments . Broad Audience : It is beneficial for anyone who practices veterinary dentistry, including specialists, general practitioners, students , and technicians . Enhanced Visuals : Full-color images aid in comprehension and make this a valuable visual resource. Comprehensive Coverage : The book is a comprehensive yet user-friendly reference on periodontal disease in dogs and cats.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/61krNoPmK0L._SL1360.jpg?v=1757789281', '', 'Cats', '["cat","dentistry-1","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10739959136559', 'Small Animal Endoscopy, An Issue of Veterinary Clinics of North America: Small Animal Practice, E-Book (The Clinics: Veterinary Medicine)', 35, 'Your Guide to Small Animal Endoscopy This book is a valuable resource that brings considerable expertise to the topic of Small Animal Endoscopy . Top experts discuss minimally invasive surgical (MIS) procedures, including surgical technique, case selection, outcome, and complications. Articles also cover the available technology to augment MIS, developments on skills training opportunities, and the future of veterinary robotic surgery. Key Features In-Depth Clinical Reviews : Provides in-depth clinical reviews on small animal endoscopy, offering actionable insights for clinical practice . Relevant Topics : Contains 11 relevant, practice-oriented topics , including new training options for small animal minimally invasive surgeons; advances in minimally invasive procedures of the thoracic cavity; advances in the treatment of canine chylothorax; and new technology augmenting veterinary minimally invasive surgery. Latest Information : Presents the latest information on this timely, focused topic under the leadership of experienced editors in the field. Authors synthesize and distill the latest research and practice guidelines to create clinically significant, topic-based reviews. Future of Veterinary Surgery : Articles also cover the future of veterinary robotic surgery .', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/71H_5zpCevL._SL1500.jpg?v=1757243610', '', 'Cats', '["cat"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10739950551343', 'Diseases of Senior Cats and Dogs. Diagnosis and Therapy II ed', 35, 'Your Comprehensive Guide to Geriatric Medicine This book comprehensively covers geriatric medicine for dogs and cats , providing a different approach to clinically useful information. All chapters have been rigorously reviewed and updated, with a particular emphasis on pharmacological protocols, dosages, and new therapies. Key Features Pharmacological Updates : The book places a particular emphasis on updated pharmacological protocols and dosages , as well as new therapies . New Endocrine Chapter : An entire new chapter on endocrine problems in senior pets has been added. Target Audience : The book is for veterinary surgeons and students approaching the end of their veterinary medicine degree, offering a unique perspective on geriatric care. Rigorous Review : All chapters have been rigorously reviewed and updated to ensure the content is current and authoritative.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/61lxMJ1J9bL._SL1200.jpg?v=1757238914', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10739948093743', 'Clinical Atlas of Canine and Feline Dermatology 1st Edition', 55, 'Your Visual Guide to Canine and Feline Dermatology This book presents more than a thousand high-quality color photographs depicting common dermatologic diseases and conditions, making it easy for clinicians to quickly evaluate and accurately identify clinical dermatologic lesions. Written by experienced veterinary dermatologists, the book begins with chapters on essential dermatologic diagnostics and the identification and interpretation of skin lesions. Key Features Extensive Visuals : Provides more than 1,200 images showing the most encountered dermatologic conditions in dogs and cats. Easy-to-Use Charts : Includes easy-to-interpret charts of differential diagnoses and treatments , helping practitioners quickly find the most common differential diagnoses, perform appropriate diagnostics, and treat their patients. Diagnostic Algorithms : Offers diagnostic and treatment algorithms for the most common skin diseases in dogs and cats. Video Resources : Features video clips on a companion website demonstrating dermatologic diagnostic techniques, including skin scrapings and cytology, aspiration of skin masses for cytology, and biopsy. Quick Reference : Presents details of the presentation, diagnosis, and management of hundreds of skin diseases in tables for quick reference. Broad Audience : An essential book for any small animal practitioner or veterinary student .', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/81oHxqbj6VL._SL1500.jpg?v=1757237833', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","dermatology"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10717679714607', 'A Colour Atlas of Companion Animal Parasites: Life Cycles and Morphological Identification', 29, 'A Visual Guide to Companion Animal Parasites This book is a comprehensive color atlas for identifying common parasites of dogs, cats, and horses. It uses simple morphological features and presents parasite life cycles in a straightforward, accurate manner. Key Features Morphological Identification : The book provides a guide for the morphological identification of both adult parasites and their immature stages in tissues, with special consideration given to differential identification. Comprehensive Coverage : It covers the general features of major arthropods, helminths, and protozoa of dogs, cats, and horses. Climate Change and Parasites : It addresses major parasites of companion animals that may shift regions due to climate change, animal movement, and other factors. Practical Resource : With 600 parasite specimens photographed and annotated, the book mirrors what a practitioner might view down a microscope, making it a complete and practical resource for veterinary students, veterinarians, and anyone interested in parasite control.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/61AIQmeX0UL.jpg?v=1754611781', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10720951271727', 'Diagnostic MRI in Dogs and Cats 1st Edition', 45, 'Your Accessible Guide to Diagnostic MRI in Dogs and Cats Diagnostic MRI in Dogs and Cats is the first reference textbook to provide a well-illustrated and comprehensive overview of the current knowledge in veterinary clinical MRI. It makes the vast and increasingly complex topic of clinical MRI in small animals accessible to all veterinarians, focusing on imaging appearance rather than on clinical signs or treatment. Key Features Evidence-Based and Practical : It includes both evidenced-based material and the authors'' personal experience, providing an excellent overview of current knowledge in the field. Concise and Organized : Bullet points and table summaries keep the concepts concise and organized. Chapters on physics and MRI technology are concise and accessible, using many visual aids and diagrams. Rich Visuals : It is richly illustrated with over 650 annotated images showcasing the main features of disease processes. The images are obtained at all magnet field strengths, reflecting the current reality of veterinary MRI. Integrated Knowledge : Within each anatomical section, each chapter focuses on a disease category of that body region, reviewing the pathophysiology and detailing imaging features of prognostic relevance. Target Audience : This practical yet thoroughly comprehensive book is primarily an evidence-based learning resource for trainees but will also aid practicing veterinarians who have less MRI experience.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/Screenshot2025-08-11at11.23.34AM.webp?v=1754929487', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10728374567215', 'Small Animal Ophthalmic Atlas and Guide 2nd edition', 29, 'Your Quick-Reference Guide to Small Animal Ocular Conditions Small Animal Ophthalmic Atlas and Guide, Second Edition, is designed to offer a quick reference to common ocular conditions in dogs and cats. With high-quality color photographs to facilitate diagnosis and details on each condition, this book is an essential reference for small animal general practitioners, students, residents, and interns. Key Features Quick Reference : The image section is organized by area of the eye, making it easy to find and compare images to make a diagnosis. The disease section is carefully targeted to the most crucial details for developing a management plan. Extensive Visuals : The Second Edition includes significantly more images than the previous edition, with updates to images to include more representative examples where possible. Comprehensive Coverage : It includes information on a wide range of topics, including orbital disease, eyelid and adnexal disease, corneal and conjunctival disease, anterior uveal conditions, lenticular disease, the posterior segment, and the recognition and management of glaucoma. Companion Website : A companion website provides video clips to further enhance your learning experience. Broad Audience : It is an essential reference for small animal general practitioners, students, residents, and interns, and can also be used as a reference to show examples to clients.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/81ek4HfDpXL._SL1500.jpg?v=1755884404', '', 'Cats', '["cat"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10728638284079', 'Point-of-Care Ultrasound Techniques for the Small Animal Practitioner 2nd Edition', 35, 'Your Definitive Guide to Point-of-Care Ultrasound, 2nd Edition This book is a thorough revision and update to the first landmark book that presented a standardized approach to focused point-of-care ultrasound (POCUS) exams . The second edition continues to be a state-of-the-art reference for using abbreviated ultrasound exams in clinical practice, incorporating new applications and covering additional species. Key Features Standardized Approach : Presents a standardized approach to POCUS as an extension of the physical exam, including trauma, non-trauma, and monitoring applications. New Techniques : Includes coverage of new techniques for focused ultrasound exams, such as ultrasound-guided nerve blocks , musculoskeletal, brain imaging, and rapid assessment for treatable forms of shock. Expanded Species Coverage : Adds cats, exotic and wildlife mammals , and marine mammals to the existing canine coverage. Integration for Patient Care : Emphasizes the integration of POCUS techniques for optimizing patient care and accurate patient assessment. Companion Website : Offers access to a companion website with supplementary video clips of clinically relevant POCUS techniques. Broad Audience : An essential resource for a wide range of veterinary professionals, from general practitioners to specialists, and veterinary students.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/81RTVRww0XL._SL1500.jpg?v=1755960467', '', 'Cats', '["cat"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10738760122671', 'Ear, Nose and Throat Diseases of the Dog and Cat 1st Edition', 45, 'Your Definitive Guide to Ear, Nose, and Throat Diseases in Dogs and Cats This book is the ultimate reference for veterinarians and other professionals trying to diagnose and treat both common and less frequently diagnosed diseases and conditions of the ear, nose, and throat . The book is divided into four sections and provides a detailed and extensive review of the diseases of the pinna, external ear canal, middle ear and inner ear, nasal cavities and sinuses, and the pharynx and larynx. Key Features Comprehensive Coverage : It provides a detailed and extensive review of the diseases of the pinna, external ear canal, middle ear and inner ear, nasal cavities and sinuses, and the pharynx and larynx. Diagnostic Procedures : Each of the first three sections begins by discussing anatomy and physiology and then reviews a wide variety of diagnostic procedures, including video-endoscopic examination, radiography, advanced imaging , and histopathological examination of biopsy samples. Surgical Management : The final section opens with a chapter on perioperative management , with subsequent chapters that cover surgery of the ear, nose, and throat . Extensive Visuals : It is extensively referenced and includes nearly 500 color illustrations to assist in diagnosis and treatment. Broad Audience : An invaluable resource for both veterinarians in training and in practice for the accurate diagnosis and management of diseases of the ear, nose, and throat.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/81-lGoKe2NL._SL1500.jpg?v=1757025279', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10738868224303', 'The Veterinary Workbook of Small Animal Clinical Cases (Veterinary Skills Series) Workbook Edition', 29, 'A Bridge from Classroom to Clinic: Your Small Animal Practice Workbook This workbook is intended to be a bridge between classroom learning and clinical training, designed to improve patient care and clinician confidence in practice. Common presentations in small animal practice are presented as real-world case studies while the reader is guided through work-up, critical thinking, and problem-solving to run the consultation efficiently. Key Features Problem-First Approach : The aim is to present a problem-first approach and to encourage readers to think like clinicians rather than students by instilling a case-based problem-solving approach. Comprehensive Coverage : Key concepts of anatomy, physiology, radiology, clinical pathology, medicine, and surgery are covered, and readers are guided through history-taking and diagnostics to perform an effective consultation. Real-World Cases : Cases discussed include vaccinating the new kitten, castrating the new puppy, the puppy with diarrhea, the blind cat, the head-shaking dog , and the itchy dog . Categorized Complaints : Categories of complaints covered include body weight, urinary problems, the digestive system, respiratory issues, eye problems, skin and soft tissue complaints, cardiovascular, reproductive, aural, and neurological complaints . Practical Learning : The workbook guides you through work-up, critical thinking , and problem-solving to run the consultation efficiently.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/61DjiKuuX4L._SL1000.jpg?v=1757032233', '', 'Cats', '["cat","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10754981855535', 'Diagnostic Imaging for Veterinary Technicians, 2nd edition', 39, 'Your Comprehensive Guide to Veterinary Diagnostic Imaging This book is a comprehensive diagnostic imaging textbook that includes detailed positioning information for radiographic studies in the small animal clinic. The text showcases a systematic approach to the positioning of feline, canine, equine, and exotic animal patients for routine and special radiographic procedures, including dentistry procedures. Key Features Systematic Approach : The text showcases a systematic approach to the positioning of feline, canine, equine, and exotic animal patients. Comprehensive Coverage : It provides detailed positioning information for radiographic studies in the small animal clinic, including dentistry procedures . Broad Species Coverage : It covers feline, canine, equine, and exotic animal patients for routine and special radiographic procedures. Target Audience : This book is an essential guide for veterinary technicians and students who want to master diagnostic imaging. Practical Focus : The book is a comprehensive diagnostic imaging textbook with a focus on practical application in the small animal clinic.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/61cyScR9P5L._SL1500.jpg?v=1759003064', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10754980675887', 'Handbook on Animal-Assisted Therapy 6th Edition', 45, 'Your Leading Reference for Animal-Assisted Therapy, 6th Edition This book continues to be the leading textbook and reference in the field of animal-assisted therapy (AAT) for clinical practitioners. This new, fully updated edition provides the evidence basis for the effectiveness of this treatment, as well as clear guidelines on how to perform it—from the selection of the therapy animal to application with patients. Key Features Comprehensive Structure : Organized into four sections, the book explores the conceptualization of the animal-human bond , best practices for AAI professionals, considerations related to animal selection/training/welfare, and utilizing AAI in special populations. New and Updated Content : Contains 15 new chapters covering culture, research, standards of practice, and more, ensuring the information is current and comprehensive. Practical Guidance : It guides readers on how to work with a therapy animal safely and effectively. Targeted Applications : The book covers AAT with special populations and for specific disorders. Certification Support : It summarizes current research on AAT and supports study for the Animal-Assisted Intervention Specialist Certification Exam .', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/615zLDrdxXL._SL1278.jpg?v=1759002702', '', 'Cats', '["cat","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10754977693999', '[December 31, 2024] The Busy Vet''s Guide to Cytology: What Do All the Blobs Mean?', 49, 'Your Indispensable Guide to Veterinary Cytology in Practice This book is an indispensable, in-practice guide to using cytology in everyday veterinary practice . It outlines the basics of cytological examination and explores how to work with cytology results as a diagnostic tool alongside other treatments and assessments. The book is accessible and digestible, designed to be an aid to busy vets in practice. Key Features Comprehensive Techniques : It covers acquiring and preparing cytological specimens, staining slides , and microscope use . Body System Approach : The book addresses general principles of veterinary cytology and then takes a body-system approach applied to all veterinary patients. Diagnostic Integration : It explores how to work with cytology results as a diagnostic tool alongside other treatments and assessments. Case Resolution : The guide includes working with labs, a round-up of difficult cases , and digital cytology . Interpretation : It focuses on interpreting samples from common locations to provide clear and actionable results. Broad Audience : This indispensable aid is perfect for vets in practice who need a quick, reliable reference.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/81CSXgLgT9L._SL1500.jpg?v=1759000527', '', 'Cats', '["cat","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10751558713647', 'Self-Assessment Colour Review of Feline Infectious Diseases 1st Edition', 35, 'A Case-Based Guide to Feline Infectious Diseases This book covers all types of feline infectious diseases , including infections caused by viruses, bacteria, parasites, and fungi. 199 clinical cases are presented randomly, as in practice, and cover the range of infectious diseases that affect all the organ systems of the cat. Key Features Case-Based Approach : 199 clinical cases are presented randomly, as in practice, to simulate real-life situations. Integrated Learning : The illustrated clinical cases contain integrated questions and detailed explanatory answers , making it a valuable self-assessment tool. Comprehensive Coverage : It covers the range of infectious diseases that affect all the organ systems of the cat . Broad Audience : The book is designed for professionals in practice and in universities , as well as for veterinary students, veterinary nurses , and technicians .', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/91Jo8fQadbL._SL1500.jpg?v=1758704725', '', 'Cats', '["cat","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10751556649263', 'Equine Internal Medicine: Self-Assessment Color Review Second Edition 2nd Edition', 35, 'Your Case-Based Guide to Equine Internal Medicine, 2nd Edition This book is a valuable resource that presents more than 200 interesting and challenging cases encountered in equine practice. Completely revised and updated, this new edition of a bestseller contains entirely new cases, presented in a random order, just as they would appear in practice. Key Features Case-Based Approach : The cases are formatted as self-assessment problems comprising integrated questions, illustrations, and detailed explanations designed to educate as well as to provide answers. Comprehensive Coverage : The book covers a wide range of disciplines, including neurology, cardiology, respiratory disease, gastroenterology, urology, infectious diseases, parasitology, hematology, oncology, endocrinology, reproduction, dermatology, ophthalmology, immunology , and musculoskeletal disorders . Broad Audience : Whether preparing for exams or continuing your professional development, this book gives you a firm foundation in how to assess, diagnose, and treat a wide variety of cases. Expert Authorship : Written by well-respected experts from the UK and USA, the book provides a high level of detail and practical information. Detailed Explanations : The authors include pertinent questions with each case to guide you through the case workup and treatments with in-depth answers for each case in the second half of the book.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/Screenshot2025-09-24at4.02.19AM.webp?v=1758704594', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10751555731759', 'Cattle and Sheep Medicine: Self-Assessment Color Review 2nd ed. Edition', 49, 'A Case-Based Guide to Cattle and Sheep Medicine, 2nd Edition This book incorporates over 250 new clinical cases divided equally between cattle and sheep. The cases appear randomly to reflect real-life practice and are presented as a set of integrated questions, photographs, and detailed explanatory answers to educate, not just to test. The book covers important clinical features of a range of common diseases of ruminants encountered in first-opinion practice in a problem-based format. Key Features Case-Based Format : It includes over 250 new clinical cases that are presented randomly to reflect real-life practice. Each case is presented as a set of integrated questions, photographs, and detailed explanatory answers. Problem-Based Learning : The book covers important clinical features of a range of common diseases of ruminants encountered in first-opinion practice in a problem-based format . Updated Content : The book also contains many diseases not featured in the former edition. While common diseases are also again featured, the situations have been changed to mimic general practice, as a disease does not always manifest with the same clinical features. Practical Treatment : The diagnosis and treatment regimens described are those used by the author over the past 38 years in commercial large animal practice. They acknowledge the time and financial restrictions that occur in many situations but require no specialized facilities or equipment. Revision Tools : New images have been added for all cases, and multiple-choice questions are included for revision purposes.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/Screenshot2025-09-24at3.59.00AM.webp?v=1758704377', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","dogs"]');
INSERT INTO Products (id, title, price, description, image, download_link, category, collections) VALUES ('10751555240239', 'Avian Medicine and Surgery: Self-Assessment Color Review, 2nd Edition', 29, 'Your Quick Reference to Avian Medicine and Surgery, 2nd Edition This completely revamped second edition of a leading text includes over 260 all-new color illustrated cases , with questions and answers fully exploring a breadth of diseases and disorders. This book provides a unique quick reference for clinicians and a useful self-test for students by offering comprehensive, clinically-oriented information that can be quickly accessed, easily understood, and applied. Key Features Case-Based Approach : The cases are presented in a random order , just as they would appear in daily practice, challenging the reader to address real clinical situations and offering a comprehensive solution. Comprehensive Coverage : The book covers a wide range of disciplines, organ systems, and species, providing a comprehensive, clinically-oriented approach to avian care. Self-Assessment : The book is a useful self-test for students , with questions and answers that fully explore a breadth of diseases and disorders. Expert Authorship : It includes contributions from leading international authorities with diverse fields of expertise, ensuring the content is authoritative and up-to-date. Broad Audience : A unique quick reference for clinicians and a useful self-test for students , this book is designed to support a wide range of veterinary professionals. Visual Learning : The book includes over 260 all-new color illustrated cases , with questions and answers that fully explore a breadth of diseases and disorders.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0928/9338/0911/files/71Au2ILHrhL._SL1500.jpg?v=1758703991', '', 'Cats', '["cat","veterinary-medicine","dogs"]');
